      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): preserve structured tool result visible text",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Preserve structured non-image tool-result blocks as visible text in the subscription/display path.\n- Add a narrow structured fallback in `extractToolResultText`.\n- Add focused tests for structured non-image content and mixed text/image content.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\nThe visible tool-result extraction path can drop structured non-image content because it only collects explicit text blocks. When a tool returns JSON/resource blocks without a text block, the visible transcript can fall back to an attachment placeholder instead of useful text.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add `stringifyStructuredToolResultContent` in `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.tools.ts`.\n- Skip `text` and `image` blocks in the structured fallback.\n- Serialize structured non-image blocks with circular guard and data-URI redaction.\n- Keep existing text blocks unchanged.\n\n## Tests\n- Added `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.tools.test.ts`\n  - structured non-image blocks are serialized into visible text\n  - text blocks remain intact while image blocks are skipped\n\n## Evidence\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.tools.test.ts`\n\n## Scope And Limitations\nThis PR is intentionally narrow and only addresses the visible tool-result text extraction path. The currently running local OpenClaw instance still needs a clean rebuild/reinstall path for runtime verification.\n\nRefs #97267\n",
        "branch": "fix/local-tool-result-display-placeholder",
